Subject: Navier-Stokes Local Pressure Projection Formula Extraction

Description: Source-bound extraction of the local pressure projection structure needed by the projection-remainder admission gate.

& [NavierStokesLocalPressureProjectionFormulaExtraction] is a source_bound_extraction record
  + [project] is seven math problems
  + [created_at] is 2026-06-27
  + [reentry_commit] is 7b84d19 Add Navier-Stokes projection remainder gate
  + [parent_gate] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\seven_math_problems\proof_inquiry\Navier_Stokes_Projection_Remainder_Admission_Gate.sop
  + [source] is Wolf, On the local pressure of the Navier-Stokes equations and related systems
  + [source_url] is https://arxiv.org/pdf/1611.01482
  + [authority_boundary] is source extraction only
  + [not_claimed] is no source-tail mapping, no local pressure smallness, and no Navier-Stokes regularity proof

& [ExtractedOperatorStructure] is the usable formula surface
  + [projection_object] is E_q^* projection onto gradient-field distributions
    = source_anchor: introduction lines describe projection E_q and dual projection E_q^* with E_q^*(grad_q p) = grad_q p
    = project_meaning: the relevant comparison object is not raw pressure but the gradient-field component selected by the projection
  + [pressure_representation] is partial_t grad p_h plus grad p_0
    = source_anchor: abstract and introduction state every admissible distribution can be represented by partial_t grad p_h plus grad p_0, with grad p_h similar to u and p_0 similar to forcing/tensor terms
    = project_meaning: project tail components must be assigned to p_h, p_0, or remaining projection/error terms before any CKN pressure comparison
  + [domain_locality] is subdomain G compactly contained in Omega
    = source_anchor: source formulates pressure functions p_h,G and p_0,G for subdomains G compactly contained in Omega
    = project_meaning: active balls/local entropy balls must be checked as admissible G-level local pressure domains
  + [navier_stokes_tensor_slot] is A = u tensor u minus viscosity times grad u
    = source_anchor: source names Navier-Stokes as modeled by A = u otimes u - nu grad u
    = project_meaning: far-field or cutoff terms must be expressed as part of the tensor/source side before projection-remainder matching

